set oven to 450
measure a 2 cup measuring cup
 *1 1/2 cup milk
add
 *1 cup stone-ground cornmeal
 *1/2 tsp salt
combine in a bowl
rest at least 5 minutes
 *1 cup flour
 *1 tbsp baking powder
 *1 tbsp sugar
beat in an other bowl
 *2 eggs
stir in
 *2-3 tbsp oil or melted butter or bacon fat
stir in milk mixture
add to dry ingredients
stir until just moistened

bake to 195 internal
cast iron pan 20-25 minutes
square pan 20-25 minutes
muffin pan 10-12 minutes

----heat pan in oven for crispy crust
----with buttermilk
use 
 *3/4 cup milk
 *3/4 cup buttermilk
leavening
 *1 tsp baking powder
 *1/2 tsp baking soda
----
add to dry ingredients
 *up to 1/2 cup sugar
 *up to 1 tbsp chili powder
add to wet ingredients
 *up to 1/2 cup honey
 *up to 2 fresh or roasted and skinned jalapenno
 *up to 1 roasted and skinned red bell pepper
 *up to 4 oz canned drained green pepper
 *up to 1/2 cup corn
 *up to 1 cooked chopped onion
 *up to 4 sliced green onion
fold in at the end
 *up to 1 cup grated cheddar or montery jack
 *up to 1/2 cup bacon or ham

